// Collectibles: Vacation Photos (DLC01) (20 items)
static const CollectibleData island01_photos_data[] = {
    {"Camping ground", "collectable_photo_12", "A photo taken at the Vråkudden camping ground.\nOn the back of the photo, it reads: \"Goodbye for now, Vråkudden! Maria is fed up with us \"freezing our butts off every summer for the last 10 years. So next summer will be Andalusia...\"", 4436.444336f, 1131.235352f, -673.213867f},
    {"Cave entrance", "collectable_photo_13", "On the back of the photo, it reads: \"Alright, Bergsfrugrottan, here we come! Break a leg, haha.\"", 4547.533203f, 1169.065552f, -39.196114f},
    {"Cinnamon buns", "collectable_photo_15", "On the back of the photo, it reads: \"Sabiha's Little Café in Himarvet. Best cinnamon buns in the whole world, and cosiest place you could ever imagine. All my childhood rolled up into one tiny delicacy. Too bad my leave is ending tonight.\"", 4325.256348f, 1029.534058f, 217.163620f},
    {"Hunting club", "collectable_photo_17", "On the back of the photo, it reads: \"Hunting Club, autumn of 1989. Most of the gang is there today.\nOn the photo: Ingvar Larsson, John Wilson\nBehind the camera: Per-Erik Lindqvist\nMissing: Bengt Öjlert (stuck at work over the weekend again, Ingvar said)\"", 3145.365967f, 1121.093384f, -188.421188f},
    {"Indian summer", "collectable_photo_09", "A vacation photo taken on the beach at Tärnboda skans.\nOn the back of the photo, it reads: \"September 22nd, at 4 pm. What a lovely day! Tomas even swam for a bit.\"", 5345.628906f, 1027.474854f, -413.742188f},
    {"Klacksundsfyren", "collectable_photo_04", "A picture of the lighthouse of Klacksundsfyren, dated from June 1986.\nOn the back of the photo, it reads:\n\"Greger and the kids just left. Guess it's just you and me once more, my friend. Aunt Viktoria won't leave you alone.\" ", 3456.500488f, 1155.921265f, -779.082153f},
    {"Lookout point", "collectable_photo_16", "Taken from the top of the lookout point at Vålklacken.\nOn the back of the photo, it reads: \"Summer 1988. Breathtaking view, worst day ever. Dad panted heavily the whole way up, and blamed me for his painful knees for weeks after that.\"", 3873.021729f, 1078.760742f, -337.809998f},
    {"Panorama of Himfjäll", "collectable_photo_14", "A panorama of the Himfjäll, with Östervik visible in the far distance.\nOn the back of the photo, it reads: \"I won the bet! The colonel will kill us if he finds out I climbed the antenna for this.\"", 3967.262695f, 1052.117432f, 51.518143f},
    {"Party time at Björntunet", "collectable_photo_10", "On the back of the photo, it reads: \"Good job wasting our last picture, Frances! Seriously, how come my thumb is ALWAYS in the shot?\"", 5498.486816f, 1074.753540f, -91.073112f},
    {"Per-Erik and Barbro Lindqvist at Björntunet", "collectable_photo_03", "A seemingly well-off couple posing in front of Björntunet Hotel. On the back of the photo, someone wrote in a very elegant handwriting:\n\"29/10/1989. Barbro and me, the day after we arrived. The place hasn't changed much since last time. Note to self: this time, enjoy the spa and massages in between business meetings.\"", 3429.031494f, 1183.852905f, -463.064819f},
    {"Restricted area", "collectable_photo_07", "A blurry, rushed shot of what seems to be a restricted area. \nOn the back of the photo, someone scribbled hastily:\n\"Phew, the guards didn't catch us. That was close! What the hell is FOA doing in there? Uncle Calle said it's all a big alien cover-up...\"", 3810.135254f, 1090.309326f, -721.166199f},
    {"Rune stone", "collectable_photo_01", "A photo of the rune stone at Gudlög's stone ship. On the back of the photo, it reads:\n\"05/11/1989. Hope this is not blurry - really gotta double-check the translation for these runes when we get back home. Fun fact: Arthur, Percy and Morgan were hiding behind the stone.\" ", 2686.526367f, 1066.433350f, -157.665527f},
    {"Scenic view from the Björntunet Hotel", "collectable_photo_11", "A photo taken from the restaurant in the Björntunet Hotel.\nOn the back of the photo, someone wrote this in French:\n\"Last \"fika\" before my flight back home. I'm gonna miss this view... and Sweden.\"", 4572.943359f, 1166.276367f, -442.493134f},
    {"Ski slope at Himarvet", "collectable_photo_08", "A photo of the ski piste and sled slope, seen from the Himarvet vacation lodges. On the back of the photo, it reads: \"Matilda, Thomas and the others will be skiing the whole day again. Nick and I tried to take a couple of beginner lessons yesterday, but after I busted my knee, we decided to stay in today. Our agenda: hot chocolate, cinnamon buns and (very) gentle hiking!\"", 4828.016602f, 1028.927490f, -937.639343f},
    {"Skiers on the slope", "collectable_photo_05", "On the back of the photo, it reads:\n\"Sunday November 5th. Paul, Rich and Lauren on the morning of our first day. The Oklahoma gang on their first vacation abroad! Most of it at least - after last night's party, Dan overslept...\"", 3342.847656f, 1024.958252f, -1155.899780f},
    {"St Charlotte Church", "collectable_photo_19", "\"October 3rd - recon trip with Wiebi and Nadine for Mirja and Alex's wedding. I love that church, this wedding is going to be so awesome. Ludwig.\"", 3054.441650f, 1049.869507f, -782.882263f},
    {"Total beginners", "collectable_photo_18", "On the back of the photo, it reads: \"The beautiful result of putting Greg and Anna on skis on their very first day without proper ski lessons. I laughed so hard that my stomach still hurts! Greg and Anna, not so much.\"", 3121.443848f, 1135.429321f, -329.410156f},
    {"View of Djupskäret", "collectable_photo_20", "A picture of the small island of Djupskäret, seen from the outskirts of Österhällan.", 4138.712402f, 1076.003052f, -854.792664f},
    {"Wedding reception", "collectable_photo_06", "The \"Before\" shot of a wedding reception.\nOn the back of the photo, it reads:\n\"November 9th, 16:15. Everything's (more or less) ready! Hope Mirja and Alex will like it. I'm not a fan of the plastic chairs, though. Not very wedding-y.\"", 3070.792236f, 1057.899536f, -1041.566772f},
    {"Wooden bridge at Gäddön", "collectable_photo_02", "A picture of the villa at Gäddön. On the back of the photo, it reads:\n\"Taken on 15/09/1989. Def. my favorite. Brings back so many memories. Use this one for the classified.\" ", 3183.622803f, 1035.482178f, 50.670017f},
};
// Collectibles: World (7 items)
static const CollectibleData location_lore_data[] = {
    {"Archipelago Region", "collectable_location_01_archipelago", "At the southeastern tip of Östertörn is a small archipelago of islands consisting of Norra Saltholmen, Södra Saltholmen, Iboholmen and a variety of smaller islands. \n\nIt is an area of historical relevance, with the great Iboholmen Castle standing proud for several centuries before finally being destroyed during the Russian Pillage at the end of the Great Northern War. In more recent times the army has established a naval base on Södra Saltholmen, in place to deter the old Russian nemesis from trying again.", -7016.086426f, 1095.652710f, -1591.216064f},
    {"Farmlands Region", "collectable_location_03_farmlands", "The fertile soils of inner Östertörn have been used for agriculture for thousands of years, ever since the post-Ice Age isostasy raised what used to be a seabed above the surface.\n\nWedged in between the Kilslagen mountains and the Tylöveden forest, these plains made the perfect location for the air force to establish their base F23 Överby - one of many similar such installations throughout Sweden.", -7016.086426f, 1095.652710f, -1591.216064f},
    {"Forest Region", "collectable_location_04_forest", "Ranging from Hagaboda in the north down to Östervik in the south, the Tylöveden forest provides recreational opportunities as well as industrial logging opportunities, and was a popular hiding place for robbers ever since the medieval period.\n\nThe other defining feature of this region is the settlement of Östervik, the municipal center of Östertörn and an important shipping port. The town is frequented not only by sailing boats during summer season, but also tankers. Some of them headed to the IGA industrial gas factory just outside of town.", -7016.086426f, 1095.652710f, -1591.216064f},
    {"Marshlands Region", "collectable_location_06_marshlands", "One of the great wilderness experiences of Östertörn is going on a hike or hunting in the Myrdalen valley of the Marshlands Region. Drawing comparisons to the rugged wilds of northern Sweden, this area is more commonly frequented by colder weather. \n\nHistorically, the marshy coastline has been a popular base of operations for many a smuggler, but that has been somewhat deterred in recent years with the opening of the Norrmyra tank battalion army base. When hiking through the wild, be sure not to enter any of their artillery range areas. ", -7016.086426f, 1095.652710f, -1591.216064f},
    {"Mountains Region", "collectable_location_05_mountains", "The Kilslagen mountains is a vast undulating area of deep forests and elevated points, providing magnificent views out across the open farmlands below.\n\nHaving been a center for ore mining in the region since the 1500s, it has in recent years been more frequently used by the army for shelters and subterranean facilities. One of the few ones known to the public in general is the Muskudden naval base, with its large subterranean docks.", -7016.086426f, 1095.652710f, -1591.216064f},
    {"North Coast Region", "collectable_location_07_north_coast", "The windswept plains of the North Coast Region can feel almost otherworldly compared to the rest of Östertörn, which has made this region a very popular spot for tourists, whether hiking across the Älvaret plains or visiting the Bronze Age hill fort of Viskandets borg. \n\nThe majority of the local populace lives in the town of Hagaboda, famous for its many historically emerging artists and painters, as well as highly sought-after Swedish limestone. ", -7016.086426f, 1095.652710f, -1591.216064f},
    {"South Coast Region", "collectable_location_02_south_coast", "The South Coast Region consists of the large peninsula called Hisinganäset, as well as the Sävered coastal area. The region is reminiscent of the Swedish west coast and is famous for its picturesque fishing villages nestled in between large coastal bedrock hills. \n\nOne of the major employers in the region is the Army, due to the Torsberga coastal fortress. The fortress itself dates back over a hundred years, but has been modernized with state-of-the-art modern artillery during the Cold War, albeit not necessarily in the public eye.", -7016.086426f, 1095.652710f, -1591.216064f},
};
// Collectibles: Love Letters (DLC02) (10 items)
static const CollectibleData love_letters_data[] = {
    {"All I Can Think About", "collectable_loveletter_04", "Jakob!\nI dream of our time together during my spring break every night. My parents keep asking why I’m saving all my allowance instead of spending it on nights out with my friends or other college luxuries. The truth is, all I can think about is returning to Sweden to be with you. Please tell me you still feel the same, that you haven’t met someone else.\nMaybe you could come visit America as well? It would definitely get my parents off my case, to see you’re a real person and not some con artist.\nPlease reply when you can, I’ll be waiting.\nHej då! (Did I spell it right? I’m trying but there aren’t many resources for learning Swedish here…)\nLove,\nAshley ", -516.082764f, 1063.137695f, 1609.799316f},
    {"Another Castle", "collectable_loveletter_02", "Elsa,\nI never thought I’d be writing with actual paper ever again. We as a society should have moved past the need for the analog by now, or I guess I thought we had. It’s all gone so sideways now, and I miss my floppies.\nI’ve been keeping a log of the various places I wind up in while searching for any other survivors. It’s not fun on my own out here against those...they look like something out of a game we could play, but worse. \nYou can stop with the whole ‘in another castle’ act any day. It would be nice to see you again.\nGod, am I starting to sound like Svante, writing to myself like this?\nWhatever, it’s keeping me sane, and we both know how impressive my brain can be. Can’t let it go to waste.\nI’ll keep searching. For anyone, for everyone. \nFor you.\n/Veronika", -1817.686279f, 1062.153564f, 1569.117798f},
    {"Crayfish", "collectable_loveletter_10", "Lotta,\nI borrowed my granddad's crayfish traps. We should put the cages out as soon as it starts getting dark. Then we need to pick them up at first light. Do you have a sleeping bag? We can have a sleepover. Bring a towel and we can use the sauna and go skinnydipping.\nKim", 64.417633f, 1024.572876f, 1972.024536f},
    {"Lov", "collectable_loveletter_06", "Lov,\nI’m sorry it’s taken me so long to write you back.\nHow have you been?\nIs the job in Malmö treating you well?\nI miss you too.\n-Bo", -473.341309f, 1056.495239f, 1275.915649f},
    {"Morning Walks", "collectable_loveletter_08", "Patrik,\nStella and I miss you. Our morning walks aren’t the same with you gone. I know the business trip is only for the year, and the reasoning for keeping us home in Sweden made sense. It doesn’t change how my heart feels. Stella asks where you are and when you’re coming home every night. \nI was thinking of planning a party for your return! Would that be okay, or would you be too bashful? Let me know, I can see if the nice restaurant in the center of Stockholm could reserve us a table. My mom could even come watch Stella for us that night, if we wanted to get a hotel…?\nCome home soon, sweetheart.\nLove,\nBritt-Marie", 689.948547f, 1024.501709f, 1247.798462f},
    {"My Person", "collectable_loveletter_03", "Sally, \n\nYou get too embarrassed when I try to tell you, so I have no option but to put it in writing: \n\nYou are my person. I am yours forever and ever and ever and ever. And ever.\n\n/Anna", -1290.703125f, 1045.066406f, 1594.723267f},
    {"My Warmth", "collectable_loveletter_07", "Meu coração,\nIt’s finally happening. I’ve finished the final payments on my flight tickets. My friends here in São Paulo don’t understand why I would choose to freeze during winter when I could stay in the warmth here. What they don’t realize is that you are my warmth.\nWell, that, and I love the snow.\nPlease buy extra kanelbulle for my visit. I’ll bring coffee--the GOOD coffee from Brazil.\nTchau!\n/Antônia", -856.507751f, 1065.830200f, 1236.583008f},
    {"No Little Games", "collectable_loveletter_09", "Hallo Yvi,\nWell, it's 2:30 am, I still can't sleep. Don't really want to either, but tomorrow will be a very busy, stressful day...\nI just felt like writing to you before going to bed. Hopefully we'll have our 3rd date before you get to read this, but anyway I just thought it would put a smile on your face.\n\nI really had a lovely evening with you today. It had been a while, and it felt really good. \nI'm so very sorry that our first kiss ended up taking place on a romantic pier at Strandvägen on a foggy night with all the Christmas decorations in the background. I'll see to it that the next kiss takes place at the Skärgård news stand, surrounded by angry businessmen and shady drunks.\n\nThanks for your kind words tonight. It's so easy to just chat with you about anything, it just feels uncomplicated and authentic. No little games, nothing for show, as it can sometimes be on dates. But still I wasn't completely sure that you felt the same. I can now tell you that my heart was pounding like crazy at the pier earlier! You're just a great person, I love the way you think and the way you say it. This is all really promising, I can't wait to see where it will take us. Danke!\n\nHave a lovely day, and don't fall asleep into your herring dish at your Christmas company party. \n\nJe t'embrasse,\nTon petit zombie\n\nPS: Oh, would you fancy going to karaoke some day? I was planning to arrange a karaoke night with my friends by the end of the year. You said that you love singing - I can guarantee you'll have a good time.", -1016.688721f, 1045.682617f, 1913.648315f},
    {"The One", "collectable_loveletter_01", "First things first, promise me you won’t tell ANYONE about what I write in this letter.\nPromise me Anders!\n...I’m trusting that you’ve sworn to the mountains that you won’t tell anyone. Now you may continue to read this letter.\nI think there is something happening between Angelica and I. She joins me for fika every day, and lately we’ve found ourselves out to dinner after late nights in the office.\nI don’t know what to do. You know I don’t have the experience you do with romantic partners. I really need your advice, I don’t want to mess this up. I think she may be the one.\n...Please don’t tell anyone. And you better not laugh at me! You’re like my brother, I’m trusting you to help me out here!\nLet me know next time you’re on the mainland, I’ll treat you to a few drinks!\nBest,\n/Mikael", -1782.814331f, 1077.498779f, 1004.863464f},
    {"Waiting", "collectable_loveletter_05", "I told you the postman would figure it out eventually, Bo. Hopefully all of the other letters reach you too.\nOr maybe it’s okay if they don’t.\nWhen will you come visit again? Train tickets are only getting more expensive, but I miss you.\nWaiting for your reply, as always.\n/Lovisa", 9.180964f, 1041.787476f, 1309.394775f},
};
